Prompt Level: 13-Advanced [SEP] Prompt: You are writing to Harry, a new manager in your company. He wants advice on how to effectively motivate his team and what strategies to avoid. Use the language and strategies you have learned in this lesson. Type in the input box. Write 150-200 words. [SEP] Response: Hello,
Sometimes it’s hard to pinpoint exactly what you should do as a manager in this situation but in my opinion those are some important hints for motivating your team. 
First, listen to them. If they feel heard they will be happier and more productive;
Second, be respectful. Treat them as you would like to be treated;
Third, you should incentive them. A reward program, for instance, like vacations vouchers or cash should be a good idea;
Fourth, try to act as their mentor and take an active interest in their careers;
Fifth, prioritize an healthy work life balance, your employees must be happy and fulfilled with their life’s outside the company and they can only achieve it if they have time doing that.
In contrast, if you disrespect your employees, gets angry with them, take credits for their work and don’t praise them when they are successful it’s the best way to get a demotivated and unproductive team. 
